Nairobi Governor Mike Mbuvi Sonko has now accused officials from the office of the auditor general of demanding for a bribe of over 100million shillings in exchange of a good audit report. Governor Sonko who was appearing before the Senate public accounts committee argued that some of the reports prepared by the auditor general were in bad faith and full of malice. Sonko also confirmed that he has so far used20 million shillings from his pocket to beautify the city.